<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="utf-8">
<title>hybrid_sim - Core Architecture</title>
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
<style>
  :root {
    --bg: #0e1116;
    --panel: #161b22;
    --panel-2: #1f2630;
    --ink: #e6edf3;
    --muted: #8b949e;
    --line: #30363d;
    --accent: #58a6ff;
    --qemu: #4c8bf5;        /* blue: QEMU */
    --qemu-soft: #1f2d4a;
    --vsim: #3fb950;        /* green: vsim/Verilator */
    --vsim-soft: #1c3324;
    --abi: #f0883e;         /* orange: shared ABI */
    --abi-soft: #3a2614;
    --danger: #f85149;
    --code-bg: #0b0f15;
  }
  * { box-sizing: border-box; }
  html, body { margin: 0; padding: 0; background: var(--bg); color: var(--ink);
    font-family: ui-sans-serif, system-ui, -apple-system, "Segoe UI", Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
    line-height: 1.55; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; }
  code, pre, .mono { font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, "JetBrains Mono", Menlo, Consolas, monospace; }
  a { color: var(--accent); text-decoration: none; }
  a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }

  header {
    padding: 28px 32px 18px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, #11161d 0%, #0e1116 100%);
  }
  header h1 { margin: 0 0 6px; font-size: 26px; letter-spacing: 0.2px; }
  header .sub { color: var(--muted); font-size: 14px; }
  .legend {
    display: flex; gap: 18px; margin-top: 14px; flex-wrap: wrap; font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted);
  }
  .legend .dot { display: inline-block; width: 10px; height: 10px; border-radius: 2px; margin-right: 6px; vertical-align: middle; }
  .dot.qemu { background: var(--qemu); }
  .dot.vsim { background: var(--vsim); }
  .dot.abi  { background: var(--abi); }

  main { max-width: 1180px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 24px 32px 80px; }
  section { margin: 36px 0; }
  h2 { font-size: 20px; margin: 0 0 14px; padding-bottom: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line); }
  h3 { font-size: 16px; margin: 18px 0 8px; color: var(--ink); }
  p { color: #c9d1d9; }

  /* ------------------------------------------------------ Architecture diagram */
  .arch {
    display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 56px 1fr 56px 1fr; gap: 0;
    align-items: stretch; margin: 8px 0 12px;
  }
  .node {
    border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: 10px; padding: 16px;
    background: var(--panel); cursor: pointer; transition: transform .12s ease, border-color .12s ease;
  }
  .node:hover { transform: translateY(-1px); border-color: var(--accent); }
  .node.active { border-color: var(--accent); box-shadow: 0 0 0 2px rgba(88,166,255,0.18); }
  .node .label { font-size: 12px; color: var(--muted); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 1px; }
  .node .title { font-weight: 600; margin: 4px 0 8px; font-size: 16px; }
  .node ul { margin: 6px 0 0; padding-left: 18px; color: #c9d1d9; font-size: 13px; }
  .node ul li { margin: 2px 0; }
  .node.qemu  { border-top: 3px solid var(--qemu); }
  .node.vsim  { border-top: 3px solid var(--vsim); }
  .arrow {
    position: relative; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;
    color: var(--muted); font-size: 11px;
  }
  .arrow svg { width: 100%; height: 28px; }
  .arrow .cap { position: absolute; top: -2px; font-size: 11px; color: var(--abi); white-space: nowrap; }
  .arrow .file { position: absolute; bottom: -6px; font-size: 11px; color: var(--muted); white-space: nowrap; }

  /* ------------------------------------------------------ Detail panel */
  .detail {
    margin-top: 12px; padding: 16px 18px; background: var(--panel-2);
    border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: 10px; min-height: 80px;
  }
  .detail h3 { margin-top: 0; }
  .detail .pill {
    display: inline-block; padding: 2px 8px; border-radius: 999px; font-size: 11px;
    background: #232a33; color: var(--muted); margin-right: 6px;
  }
  .detail .grid {
    display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 12px; margin-top: 10px;
  }
  .card {
    background: var(--panel); border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: 8px; padding: 12px 14px;
  }
  .card h4 { margin: 0 0 6px; font-size: 13px; color: var(--ink); }
  .card p, .card ul { font-size: 13px; color: #c9d1d9; margin: 0; }
  .card ul { padding-left: 18px; }
  .card code { background: var(--code-bg); padding: 1px 5px; border-radius: 3px; font-size: 12px; }
  .file-ref {
    color: var(--muted); font-size: 12px; font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, monospace;
    margin-top: 8px;
  }

  /* ------------------------------------------------------ Walkthrough */
  .walk {
    border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: 10px; background: var(--panel);
  }
  .walk-head {
    display: flex; gap: 8px; padding: 12px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
    align-items: center; justify-content: space-between; flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
  .step-btns { display: flex; gap: 6px; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .step-btn {
    background: var(--panel-2); border: 1px solid var(--line); color: var(--ink);
    padding: 6px 10px; border-radius: 6px; cursor: pointer; font-size: 12px;
    font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, monospace;
  }
  .step-btn:hover { border-color: var(--accent); }
  .step-btn.active { background: var(--accent); color: #0b0f15; border-color: var(--accent); }
  .nav-btns button {
    background: var(--panel-2); border: 1px solid var(--line); color: var(--ink);
    padding: 6px 12px; border-radius: 6px; cursor: pointer; font-size: 13px;
  }
  .nav-btns button:hover { border-color: var(--accent); }
  .nav-btns button:disabled { opacity: 0.4; cursor: not-allowed; }

  .walk-body {
    display: grid; grid-template-columns: 360px 1fr; min-height: 320px;
  }
  .walk-stage {
    position: relative; padding: 16px; border-right: 1px solid var(--line);
    background: var(--panel-2);
  }
  .walk-info { padding: 16px; }
  .stage-actor {
    border: 1px dashed var(--line); border-radius: 8px; padding: 10px;
    margin: 6px 0; transition: all .25s ease; opacity: 0.45;
  }
  .stage-actor.qemu { border-color: var(--qemu); }
  .stage-actor.vsim { border-color: var(--vsim); }
  .stage-actor.abi  { border-color: var(--abi); }
  .stage-actor.live {
    opacity: 1; box-shadow: 0 0 0 2px rgba(255,255,255,0.04), 0 4px 16px rgba(0,0,0,0.4);
    transform: translateY(-1px);
  }
  .stage-actor.live.qemu { background: var(--qemu-soft); }
  .stage-actor.live.vsim { background: var(--vsim-soft); }
  .stage-actor.live.abi  { background: var(--abi-soft); }
  .stage-actor .actor-title { font-weight: 600; font-size: 13px; }
  .stage-actor .actor-sub { color: var(--muted); font-size: 12px; margin-top: 2px; }
  .stage-arrow {
    text-align: center; color: var(--muted); font-size: 14px; line-height: 0; height: 12px;
    transition: color .25s ease;
  }
  .stage-arrow.live { color: var(--abi); }

  .walk-info h3 { margin-top: 0; color: var(--accent); }
  .walk-info .what, .walk-info .why {
    background: var(--panel-2); border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: 6px;
    padding: 10px 12px; margin: 8px 0; font-size: 13px;
  }
  .walk-info .what b, .walk-info .why b { color: var(--abi); display: block; font-size: 12px;
    text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 1px; margin-bottom: 4px; font-weight: 600; }
  .walk-info pre {
    background: var(--code-bg); border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: 6px;
    padding: 10px 12px; font-size: 12px; overflow-x: auto; color: #d4dadf; margin: 8px 0;
  }
  .walk-info .files { font-size: 12px; color: var(--muted); margin-top: 8px; font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, monospace; }

  /* ------------------------------------------------------ ABI viewer */
  .abi-grid {
    display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 12px;
  }
  .abi-block {
    background: var(--panel); border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: 8px; padding: 14px;
    position: relative;
  }
  .abi-block::before {
    content: ""; position: absolute; left: 0; top: 0; bottom: 0; width: 4px;
    background: var(--abi); border-radius: 8px 0 0 8px;
  }
  .abi-block h4 { margin: 0 0 6px; font-size: 14px; }
  .abi-block .sz { font-size: 11px; color: var(--muted); font-family: ui-monospace, Menlo, monospace; }
  .abi-block ul { margin: 6px 0 0; padding-left: 18px; font-size: 13px; color: #c9d1d9; }
  .abi-block ul li { margin: 1px 0; }
  .abi-block .note { font-size: 12px; color: var(--muted); margin-top: 6px; }

  /* ------------------------------------------------------ Misc */
  .kv {
    display: grid; grid-template-columns: 180px 1fr; gap: 6px 14px; font-size: 13px;
  }
  .kv .k { color: var(--muted); font-family: ui-monospace, Menlo, monospace; }
  footer { color: var(--muted); font-size: 12px; padding: 16px 32px 32px; text-align: center; }
  .ascii {
    background: var(--code-bg); border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 14px; overflow-x: auto; font-size: 12px; color: #c9d1d9;
  }
  details {
    background: var(--panel); border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 8px 12px; margin: 8px 0;
  }
  details summary { cursor: pointer; font-weight: 600; font-size: 14px; }
  details[open] summary { margin-bottom: 6px; }
  .tag {
    display: inline-block; padding: 1px 6px; border-radius: 3px; font-size: 11px;
    font-family: ui-monospace, Menlo, monospace; margin-right: 4px;
  }
  .tag.qemu { background: var(--qemu-soft); color: #8eb6ff; }
  .tag.vsim { background: var(--vsim-soft); color: #80df90; }
  .tag.abi  { background: var(--abi-soft); color: #f7b078; }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .arch { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .arrow { height: 36px; }
    .arrow svg { transform: rotate(90deg); }
    .walk-body { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .detail .grid, .abi-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<header>
  <h1>hybrid_sim - Core Architecture</h1>
  <div class="sub">Andes RISC-V co-simulator: QEMU 9.x (functional, MHz) + vsim (Verilator, cycle-accurate) share architectural state across a magic-CSR boundary.</div>
  <div class="legend">
    <span><span class="dot qemu"></span>QEMU (TCG functional)</span>
    <span><span class="dot vsim"></span>vsim / Verilator (cycle-accurate)</span>
    <span><span class="dot abi"></span>Shared ABI / transport</span>
  </div>
</header>

<main>

<!-- =================================================== TOP DIAGRAM =================================================== -->
<section>
  <h2>1. Three-phase round-trip</h2>
  <p>Execution starts in QEMU for fast forward, hands off to vsim at a trigger for the cycle-accurate region of interest, then hands back to a fresh QEMU to finish. Click each box to see what it contains.</p>

  <div class="arch" id="arch">
    <div class="node qemu" data-id="qemu1">
      <div class="label">Phase 1 - functional</div>
      <div class="title">QEMU 1</div>
      <ul>
        <li>TCG plugin matches entry trigger</li>
        <li>Drains GPR/FPR/CSR/V from gdbstub</li>
        <li>Writes <code>hybrid_state_v1</code>, exits</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="arrow">
      <span class="cap">hybrid_state_v1</span>
      <svg viewBox="0 0 100 28" preserveAspectRatio="none">
        <defs><marker id="m1" markerWidth="6" markerHeight="6" refX="5" refY="3" orient="auto">
          <path d="M0,0 L6,3 L0,6 z" fill="#f0883e"/></marker></defs>
        <line x1="0" y1="14" x2="92" y2="14" stroke="#f0883e" stroke-width="2" marker-end="url(#m1)"/>
      </svg>
      <span class="file">state file (atomic write)</span>
    </div>

    <div class="node vsim" data-id="vsim">
      <div class="label">Phase 2 - cycle-accurate</div>
      <div class="title">vsim (Verilator)</div>
      <ul>
        <li><code>HandoffController</code> orchestrates</li>
        <li><code>ResumeDriver</code> restores via DM</li>
        <li>RTL runs; <code>StateDrain</code> captures on exit</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="arrow">
      <span class="cap">hybrid_state_v1</span>
      <svg viewBox="0 0 100 28" preserveAspectRatio="none">
        <defs><marker id="m2" markerWidth="6" markerHeight="6" refX="5" refY="3" orient="auto">
          <path d="M0,0 L6,3 L0,6 z" fill="#f0883e"/></marker></defs>
        <line x1="0" y1="14" x2="92" y2="14" stroke="#f0883e" stroke-width="2" marker-end="url(#m2)"/>
      </svg>
      <span class="file">gdbstub P-packets</span>
    </div>

    <div class="node qemu" data-id="qemu2">
      <div class="label">Phase 3 - functional</div>
      <div class="title">QEMU 2</div>
      <ul>
        <li>Spawned with <code>-gdb -S</code></li>
        <li>State restored via P-packets</li>
        <li>Continues; exit code propagates</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div id="archDetail" class="detail">
    <h3>Click a phase above to inspect its internals.</h3>
    <p style="color: var(--muted)">Each phase exchanges the same <code>hybrid_state_v1</code> struct (defined in <code>include/hybrid/state_abi.h</code>), but uses a completely different transport at each boundary: a binary file (QEMU1 to vsim) and the GDB Remote Serial Protocol (vsim to QEMU2). The shared mmap (<code>/dev/shm</code>) is also live in tier-2 fixtures so the C heap/stack survives across all three phases.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- =================================================== COMPONENT CARDS =================================================== -->
<section>
  <h2>2. Core components</h2>
  <p>Click each card to expand. The QEMU side is one C plugin loaded into upstream QEMU; the vsim side is a set of header-only C++20 classes orchestrated by a simulator main loop.</p>

  <details open>
    <summary><span class="tag qemu">QEMU</span> qemu_plugin / hybrid_handoff.c - drain on trigger</summary>
    <div class="grid">
      <div class="card">
        <h4>Trigger detection</h4>
        <p>Translation-time callback (<code>vcpu_tb_trans</code>) inspects every 4-byte insn in the block.</p>
        <ul>
          <li><b>CSR mode (default):</b> matches <code>csrwi 0x7C0, 0</code> for enter and <code>csrwi 0x7C0, 1</code> for exit. CSR 0x7C0 is a vendor write that has no architectural effect on Andes ax45mp - hence the "magic" trigger.</li>
          <li><b>PC mode:</b> when the plugin is loaded with <code>enter_pc=0x...</code>, the CSR matcher is bypassed and only that exact vaddr fires (works on compressed insns via <code>qemu_plugin_insn_size</code>).</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h4>Register harvest</h4>
        <p>On trigger, <code>resolve_handles()</code> looks up every gdbstub register by name. The lookup is lazy because QEMU only registers the dynamic coprocessor features (FPU, V, CSR) after vcpu_init.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>32 GPR + 32 FPR + PC</li>
          <li>13 M-mode CSRs (<code>mstatus</code>, <code>mepc</code>, <code>mtvec</code>, ..., <code>satp</code>)</li>
          <li>16 <code>pmpcfg</code> + 64 <code>pmpaddr</code></li>
          <li>V CSRs (<code>vstart</code>, <code>vtype</code>, <code>vl</code>, <code>vlenb</code>, <code>vxsat</code>, <code>vxrm</code>, <code>vcsr</code>) + v0..v31 (bytes)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h4>PC sourcing quirk</h4>
        <p>The PC value comes from <code>compute_handoff_pc(site)</code> using the translation-time vaddr + insn size, <i>not</i> from the gdbstub PC register. Reason: TCG defers PC writes - after a V-extension instruction retires the live gdbstub PC can briefly lag the actual current insn.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h4>Atomic state write</h4>
        <p><code>write_state_atomic()</code> writes to <code>$outfile.tmp.$pid</code>, <code>fsync</code>s, then <code>rename()</code>s. The vsim side never sees a torn struct. After write, QEMU calls <code>exit(0)</code>.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="file-ref">qemu_plugin/hybrid_handoff.c, include/hybrid/insn_match.h, include/hybrid/state_abi.h</div>
  </details>

  <details>
    <summary><span class="tag vsim">vsim</span> HandoffController - phase dispatcher</summary>
    <div class="grid">
      <div class="card">
        <h4>Role</h4>
        <p>Glues <code>CsrTrigger</code> (decoder of magic CSRs) and <code>StateDrain</code>. The Verilator run-loop calls <code>on_retire(pc, gpr_probe)</code> once per committed PC.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h4>Decisions</h4>
        <ul>
          <li><b>HYBRID_HANDOFF_ENTER</b> - QEMU's job, vsim ignores</li>
          <li><b>HYBRID_HANDOFF_EXIT</b> - fire drain</li>
          <li><b>HYBRID_HANDOFF_RUNTIME</b> - read rs1 GPR, fire only if value==1</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h4>Passthrough merge</h4>
        <p>The vsim DM cannot read every CSR/V byte cheaply. <code>set_passthrough_input(qemu1_state)</code> caches the QEMU1 snapshot; on drain, <code>drain_with_passthrough</code> overwrites only the fresh fields (GPRs, PC, six V CSRs) and keeps the rest as-is.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h4>Exit code</h4>
        <p>When drain fires, the simulator writes the state file and exits with <code>EXIT_HANDOFF_TO_QEMU</code>. The <code>main()</code> wrapper interprets that and invokes <code>run_qemu_handback</code>.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="file-ref">hybrid_vsim/src/hybrid/handoff_controller.hpp</div>
  </details>

  <details>
    <summary><span class="tag vsim">vsim</span> ResumeDriver - restore state via Debug Module</summary>
    <div class="grid">
      <div class="card">
        <h4>Transport: RISC-V Debug Module</h4>
        <p>The vsim CPU model exposes a Debug Module over a DMI bus. <code>ResumeDriver</code> only knows about a 32-bit register interface (<code>DmiBus::write/read</code>) - SystemC details are not in this header. This makes the class trivially unit-testable with a fake bus.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h4>Two-tier CSR restore</h4>
        <ul>
          <li><b>Tier A</b> - Abstract Command writes for GPRs, DPC, mstatus.VS, vstart, vxsat, vxrm, vcsr.</li>
          <li><b>Tier B</b> - Program Buffer for V config: stage vl in x5, vtype in x6, then run <code>vsetvl x0, x5, x6</code>. Direct csrrw to vtype would set <code>vill</code>; vl is read-only.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h4>Strict ordering</h4>
        <p>Order matters because of side effects:</p>
        <ol style="margin:0; padding-left:18px; font-size:13px">
          <li>dmactive 0 to 1, halt, wait <code>allhalted</code></li>
          <li>mstatus.VS (enables V in hart)</li>
          <li>vsetvl via PB (resets vstart to 0)</li>
          <li>vstart, vxsat, vxrm, vcsr (AFTER vsetvl)</li>
          <li>GPR loop x1..x31, DPC (overwrites x5/x6 scratch - safe now)</li>
          <li>mtvec tolerant, clear cmderr, resumereq</li>
        </ol>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h4>cmderr tolerance</h4>
        <p>The Debug Spec makes <code>abstractcs.cmderr</code> sticky. A failed write of an unimplemented CSR would block every subsequent command. The driver checks cmderr after each write, W1C-clears it, and either retries via Program Buffer (<code>write_csr_abstract_or_pb</code>) or treats the slot as a no-op (<code>write_csr_tolerant</code>).</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="file-ref">hybrid_vsim/src/hybrid/resume_driver.hpp, abstract_command.hpp, program_buffer.hpp, dmi_poll.hpp</div>
  </details>

  <details>
    <summary><span class="tag vsim">vsim</span> StateDrain - capture on exit trigger</summary>
    <div class="grid">
      <div class="card">
        <h4>What it reads</h4>
        <p>Reuses ResumeDriver's DM constants. Halts the hart, reads x1..x31 + DPC via Abstract Commands. FPR/CSR/PMP/V byte arrays are not re-read from the DM - they come from the cached QEMU1 snapshot.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h4>drain_with_passthrough</h4>
        <p>When <code>HYBRID_FLAG_V</code> is set, also freshly reads the six scalar V CSRs (<code>vstart</code>, <code>vxsat</code>, <code>vxrm</code>, <code>vcsr</code>, <code>vtype</code>, <code>vl</code>). The 32 V data registers come back via the shared scratch RAM, not via DM.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h4>Error model</h4>
        <p>If the DM raises cmderr on a register read, that field is reported as <code>0</code> after a W1C clear, and the next read proceeds. A missing CSR mirrors as zero rather than corrupting the adjacent slot.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h4>Pure-logic split</h4>
        <p>The class only touches a <code>DmiBus&amp;</code>. Tests use <code>recording_bus.hpp</code> doctest fixtures to verify the exact DMI write/read sequence without needing SystemC or Verilator.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="file-ref">hybrid_vsim/src/hybrid/state_drain.hpp</div>
  </details>

  <details>
    <summary><span class="tag vsim">vsim</span> qemu_handback - spawn QEMU 2 and replay via gdbstub</summary>
    <div class="grid">
      <div class="card">
        <h4>Spawn</h4>
        <p><code>spawn_qemu()</code> forks, redirects stdin to /dev/null (so QEMU's <code>tcsetattr</code> can't SIGTTOU the parent), and execs:</p>
        <pre style="margin:6px 0; background:var(--code-bg); border:1px solid var(--line); border-radius:6px; padding:8px; font-size:11px; overflow-x:auto">qemu-system-riscv64 \
  -cpu andes-ax45mpv,vlen=512 -bios none -nographic \
  -semihosting-config enable=on,target=native \
  -gdb tcp::PORT -S \
  [tier-1] -kernel ELF \
  [tier-2] -object memory-backend-file,share=on,... -machine andes_ae350,memory-backend=mem</pre>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h4>Register-map discovery</h4>
        <p><code>discover_reg_map()</code> walks <code>target.xml</code> and every <code>xi:include</code> annex via <code>qXfer:features:read</code> (chunked because the CSR XML is ~6 KB and PacketSize is ~1000). The result is a register-name to packet-number map - the same names the QEMU plugin used on phase 1.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h4>State application</h4>
        <p><code>apply_state()</code> sends P-packets for every field. Each call is silently skipped if the register name is not advertised (some QEMU builds omit PMP slots or extension CSRs).</p>
        <ul>
          <li>x1..x31 + PC (hard-coded numbers 1..32)</li>
          <li>FPR f0..f31 (if FP flag)</li>
          <li>13 M-mode CSRs + 16 pmpcfg + 64 pmpaddr</li>
          <li>v0..v31 as <code>vlenb</code>-byte payloads + 6 V CSRs (if V flag)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h4>Continue and propagate</h4>
        <p>After <code>sess.cont()</code>, the parent <code>waitpid()</code>s and returns QEMU2's exit code. If QEMU2 dies before the gdbstub port becomes reachable (bad <code>--qemu-binary</code> path), <code>ChildExitedDuringConnect</code> surfaces that status instead of hanging.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="file-ref">hybrid_vsim/src/hybrid/qemu_handback.hpp, gdbstub_session.hpp, reg_names.h</div>
  </details>

  <details>
    <summary><span class="tag abi">ABI</span> hybrid_state_v1 - the wire contract</summary>
    <div class="grid">
      <div class="card">
        <h4>Single source of truth</h4>
        <p><code>include/hybrid/state_abi.h</code> defines the binary layout. Both the QEMU plugin (C) and vsim (C++) include this header. Layout is locked by <code>state_abi_check.h</code> static_asserts.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h4>Versioning</h4>
        <ul>
          <li>Magic: <code>0x42594841</code> ('AHYB')</li>
          <li>Current version: 1</li>
          <li>Forward-compat: never repurpose offsets in v1 - grow via <code>reserved[232]</code> or introduce v2 alongside.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h4>Flags</h4>
        <ul>
          <li><code>HYBRID_FLAG_RV64</code> - always set</li>
          <li><code>HYBRID_FLAG_FP</code> - set only if QEMU advertised D-extension and FPR handles bound</li>
          <li><code>HYBRID_FLAG_V</code> - set only if QEMU exposed vlenb &gt; 0</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Receivers MUST check flags before consuming the matching state blocks.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h4>Sizing</h4>
        <p><code>HYBRID_VLEN_BYTES_MAX = 64</code> (VLEN=512). Driven by <code>NDS_VLEN</code> in <code>data/configs/ax45mpv_premium.cfg</code> - changing the configured VLEN means updating this constant in lock-step.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="file-ref">include/hybrid/state_abi.h, include/hybrid/state_abi_check.h</div>
  </details>

  <details>
    <summary><span class="tag abi">ABI</span> V-state transport - the trickiest piece</summary>
    <div class="grid">
      <div class="card">
        <h4>Why scalar V CSRs are split</h4>
        <p><b>Tier A (Abstract):</b> vstart, vxsat, vxrm, vcsr, mstatus.VS - plain CSR writes work because they have no architectural side effect on vtype/vl.</p>
        <p><b>Tier B (Program Buffer):</b> vtype and vl must come from <code>vsetvl x0, x5, x6</code>. A direct csrrw to vtype sets <code>vill</code>; vl is read-only outside of vsetvl. Only vsetvl restores both atomically.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h4>Why V data regs need a scratch region</h4>
        <p>The RISC-V Debug Spec does not allocate Abstract Command slots for v0..v31, and the AX45MPV CPU wrapper exports no DPI probe for the V regfile.</p>
        <p>Workaround: a reserved 2 KiB region at <code>kVScratchGpa</code> inside the shared mmap. The fixture's prologue executes <code>vle8.v vN, (t0)</code> from scratch on entry; epilogue <code>vse8.v vN, (t0)</code> on exit. vsim reads the bytes back from the host-mapped pointer (<code>read_v_from_scratch</code>).</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h4>kVScratchGpa selection</h4>
        <p><code>0x00FF0000</code> on <code>-M andes_ae350</code>, <code>0x80FF0000</code> on <code>-M virt</code>. Chosen as RAM_BASE + 0xFF0000 so the C stack (rt_c.ld places <code>_stack</code> at RAM_BASE + 0x700000) has ~9 MiB of headroom before colliding.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h4>Restore ordering recap</h4>
        <p>The strict ResumeDriver order exists because every step depends on the previous one.</p>
        <pre style="margin:0; background:var(--code-bg); border:1px solid var(--line); border-radius:6px; padding:8px; font-size:11px; overflow-x:auto">mstatus.VS = state.mstatus & 0x600
write x5 = state.vl     (Abstract)
write x6 = state.vtype  (Abstract)
PB: vsetvl x0, x5, x6   (atomic vtype+vl; resets vstart)
vstart = state.vstart
vxsat / vxrm / vcsr
GPRs x1..x31 (overwrites x5/x6)
DPC = state.pc
mtvec, resume</pre>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="file-ref">hybrid_vsim/src/hybrid/v_regfile_xfer.hpp, resume_driver.hpp; fixtures: hybrid_vsim/hybrid/test/rt_c_v_*.c</div>
  </details>
</section>

