<section>
  <h2>4. The hybrid_state_v1 ABI</h2>
  <p>Same struct, three traversals. Total size is fixed across versions; reserved bytes absorb additions.</p>

  <div class="abi-grid">
    <div class="abi-block">
      <h4>Header <span class="sz">24 B</span></h4>
      <ul>
        <li><code>magic</code> - 'AHYB' (0x42594841)</li>
        <li><code>version</code> - 1</li>
        <li><code>flags</code> - RV64 | FP | V</li>
        <li><code>hart_id</code>, <code>pc</code>, <code>priv</code></li>
      </ul>
      <div class="note">Receiver validates magic + version first; otherwise refuses.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="abi-block">
      <h4>GPR + FPR <span class="sz">512 B</span></h4>
      <ul>
        <li><code>gpr[32]</code> - x0..x31 (x0 always 0)</li>
        <li><code>fpr[32]</code> - f0..f31, valid only if HYBRID_FLAG_FP</li>
      </ul>
      <div class="note">Restored via DM Abstract Commands (vsim) and gdbstub P-packets (QEMU2).</div>
    </div>
    <div class="abi-block">
      <h4>M-mode CSRs <span class="sz">104 B</span></h4>
      <ul>
        <li><code>mstatus, mepc, mtvec, mcause, mtval, mscratch</code></li>
        <li><code>medeleg, mideleg, mip, mie, mcycle, minstret, satp</code></li>
      </ul>
      <div class="note">vsim restores only what the DM accepts; cmderr-tolerant.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="abi-block">
      <h4>PMP <span class="sz">640 B</span></h4>
      <ul>
        <li><code>pmpcfg[16]</code> - 16 8-byte slots (works for RV64 8/CSR or future RV32 4/CSR)</li>
        <li><code>pmpaddr[64]</code> - 64 region bases</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="abi-block">
      <h4>V scalar CSRs <span class="sz">32 B</span></h4>
      <ul>
        <li><code>vstart, vtype, vl, vlenb</code></li>
        <li><code>vxsat, vxrm, vcsr</code></li>
      </ul>
      <div class="note">vtype + vl restored together via <code>vsetvl</code> in Program Buffer; others via Abstract.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="abi-block">
      <h4>V data regs <span class="sz">2048 B</span></h4>
      <ul>
        <li><code>vreg[32 * 64]</code> - up to VLEN=512 bits each</li>
      </ul>
      <div class="note">DM has no slot for V regs - transported via shared scratch RAM and fixture-side vle8.v/vse8.v. QEMU2 gets them as P-packet byte payloads.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="abi-block">
      <h4>reserved <span class="sz">232 B</span></h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Zero-initialised on write</li>
        <li>Sized to keep total layout stable</li>
      </ul>
      <div class="note">v2-style additions: consume bytes here without renumbering existing offsets.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="abi-block">
      <h4>Triggers (not in struct)</h4>
      <ul>
        <li><b>CSR mode:</b> <code>csrwi 0x7C0, 0</code> enter / <code>csrwi 0x7C0, 1</code> exit</li>
        <li><b>PC mode:</b> ELF symbols <code>_hybrid_enter_pc</code> / <code>_hybrid_exit_pc</code></li>
      </ul>
      <div class="note">CSR 0x7C0 is a benign vendor write on Andes ax45mp - architecturally inert, so dropping it from real workloads is free.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

